DHT11 Temperature and Humidity Display on LCD

This project reads temperature and humidity from a DHT11 sensor and displays the values on a 16×2 LCD.
It’s useful for beginners learning how to combine sensors with displays to show real-time environmental data.

This project helps beginners learn:
-Using the DHT11 sensor with Arduino
-Reading temperature and humidity values
-Using the LiquidCrystal library to display information
-Combining sensors and displays for real-time monitoring

Arduino Code
#include <LiquidCrystal.h>
#include <DHT.h>
#include <DHT_U.h>

// LCD pins
int rs = 7;
int en = 8;
int d4 = 9;
int d5 = 10;
int d6 = 11;
int d7 = 12;

LiquidCrystal lcd(rs, en, d4, d5, d6, d7);

// DHT11 sensor
#define Type DHT11
int sensePin = 2;
float Temperature;
float Humidity;
int dts = 500;
int dt = 1000;
DHT HT(sensePin, Type);

void setup() {
  lcd.begin(16, 2); // Initialize LCD
  HT.begin();       // Initialize DHT sensor
  delay(dts);
}

void loop() {
  // Read temperature and humidity
  Temperature = HT.readTemperature();
  Humidity = HT.readHumidity();

  // Display on LCD
  lcd.clear();
  lcd.setCursor(0, 0);
  lcd.print("Temp:");
  lcd.setCursor(7, 0);
  lcd.print(Temperature);
  lcd.setCursor(13, 0);
  lcd.print("C");

  lcd.setCursor(0, 1);
  lcd.print("Umid:");
  lcd.setCursor(6, 1);
  lcd.print(Humidity);
  lcd.setCursor(13, 1);
  lcd.print("%");

  delay(10000); // Update every 10 seconds
}

Circuit Setup

Components needed:

Arduino Uno (or compatible board)
1 × DHT11 sensor
1 × 16×2 LCD
Potentiometer (10kΩ) for LCD contrast
Breadboard
Jumper wires

Wiring Instructions:

LCD
RS → pin 7
EN → pin 8
D4 → pin 9
D5 → pin 10
D6 → pin 11
D7 → pin 12
VCC → 5V
GND → GND

Contrast pin → potentiometer wiper

DHT11 Sensor
Data → pin 2
VCC → 5V
GND → GND

How it works:

The DHT11 sensor measures temperature and humidity.
Values are read using the DHT library.
The LCD displays temperature (°C) on the first row and humidity (%) on the second row.
The display updates every 10 seconds for easy reading.
